benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search - Search custom fields by type, name and optional value

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrieval (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06).
Empty Response: TC01 fetch all covers empty/data-less cases when appropriate.
Query Parameters: Numerous combinations tested (objectType, fieldName, fieldValue, audit, extra params).
Pagination: TC07 tests offset/limit; TC21 tests very large limit; TC22 tests large offset; TC30/TC31 cover performance-based timing under load.
Authorization: TC17 validates missing authentication leading to 401; TC08-TC10 cover audit-related responses requiring auth context.
Audit Integration: TC08-TC10 verify FULL/MINIMAL/NONE audit handling; TC32-TC33 address integration/degradation scenarios.
Error Handling: TC13-TC16 cover invalid parameter values; TC19-TC20 cover injection/extreme input; TC18 covers service unavailability; TC36 covers recovery from transient failures.
Regression/Backward Compatibility: TC25, TC27 address known issues and legacy behavior.
State Variations: TC28-TC29 test empty and partially populated databases.
Performance/Load: TC30-TC31 verify response time under normal/peak loads.
Accessibility/Documentation: TC34-TC35 ensure documentation and descriptive errors.
gaps: Caching Behavior: No explicit tests verifying caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache coherence.
Rate Limiting: No tests addressing rate limiting or throttling under burst traffic.
Concurrency/Race Conditions: While TC23 mentions concurrent requests, explicit race-condition scenarios or data consistency under concurrent updates are not deeply covered.
Explicit 403/Forbidden on valid authentication failure: TC17 covers missing auth (401), but explicit 403 scenarios for insufficient permissions are not described.

Granular schema validation coverage: Some tests assert array shape, but deeper per-field schema validation coverage across all query combinations could be stronger (e.g., optional/required fields in responses).
recommendations: Add explicit tests for caching behavior: verify ETag/Cache-Control headers, and cache invalidation when data changes.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to confirm proper handling under bursts.
Enhance concurrency tests to simulate race conditions (e.g., multiple updates/reads with same filters) beyond TC23.
Add tests for authorization beyond authentication failures (e.g., 403 when user lacks required permissions).
Strengthen field-level schema validation tests across more scenarios to ensure consistent response shape and types.
